snippet: The reopening reflects Israel’s effort to strengthen ties with the military-backed government in Egypt that replaced its first elected president.
abstract: Israel, as part of effort to strengthen relationship with Egypt's military-backed government, reopens embassy in Cairo; reopening comes four years to the day after prior embassy was stormed during Arab Spring uprising.
lead_paragraph: The reopening reflects Israel’s effort to strengthen ties with the military-backed government in Egypt that replaced its first elected president.

headline.main: Israel Reopens Cairo Embassy 4 Years After Protesters’ Siege
headline.print_headline: Israel Puts an Embassy Back in Egypt
